SALMONELLA, PET TREATS - CANADA: RECALL
*************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Salmonella, pig's ear dog treats - Canada (Alberta) 19990910233221
Date: Mon, 10 Jan 2000 13:51:10 -0500
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Internet Wire 10 Jan 2000

[1
Safety Alert Presence Of Salmonella Bacteria In Co-Op Gold Brand Pet Treats
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) is warning consumers not to
purchase Co-op Gold brand Hoof Delights pet treats distributed by Federated
Cooperatives Ltd. of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, because they have been found
to be contaminated by _Salmonella_ bacteria.
This product is sold in a 2-hoof pack size, with a lot number beginning
with the numbers 09291 and a UPC of 0 5731609462 9. The product is
distributed in British Columbia, Alberta, Saskatchewan, Manitoba,
Northwestern Ontario, the Northwest Territories, and Yukon.
People may risk bacterial infection by handling the treats directly or by
contact with pets who have used the treats. Elderly people, young children
and people with weakened immune systems are particularly at risk. They
should completely avoid handling the pet treats. Anyone who may have
handled the treats should wash their hands with warm water and soap.
Common symptoms of _Salmonella_ infection are nausea, vomiting, abdominal
pain, and diarrhea, and more serious consequences are possible.
The product is being voluntarily recalled by the distributor, Federated
Cooperatives Ltd. of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. Consumers should dispose of
the treats in the trash
The CFIA is monitoring the effectiveness of this recall.
***
[2
Safety Alert Presence Of Salmonella Bacteria In Rollover Brand Pet Treats
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) is warning consumers not to
purchase Rollover brand Hoof Delights pet treats manufactured by Farm Meats
Canada Ltd., of
Alberta, because they have been found to be contaminated by _Salmonella_
bacteria.
This product is sold in a 2-hoof pack size, with an 11-digit lot number
beginning with 09291 and a UPC of 0 6076688052 0. The product is
distributed across Canada. This recall does not include Rollover Rolls.
People may risk bacterial infection by handling the treats directly or by
contact with pets who have used the treats. Elderly people, young children
and people with weakened immune systems are particularly at risk. They
should completely avoid handling the pet treats. Anyone who may have
handled the treats should wash their hands with warm water and soap.
Common symptoms of _Salmonella_ infection are nausea, vomiting, abdominal
pain, and diarrhea, and more serious consequences are possible.
The product is being voluntarily recalled by the manufacturer, Farm Meats
Canada Ltd., of Alberta. Consumers should dispose of the treats in the rash.
The CFIA is monitoring the effectiveness of this recall.
